The Truth of hearts 

One day your dreams boost to success. The other you're there rethinking your past
and worrying about the future that is miles ahead of you. One day sit there excited for 
the future to come. The other you're crying afraid of what happens next in life. One day 
you're body feels like nothing can stop being happy. The other you're alone in your room
with a little voice in you're head saying you're not good enough and that's the reason you're
like this. 

This is why some hearts don't break, they just turn silent, colder, and wiser, and that is
its own tradegy. You realise the time you spend thinking great isn't going to do anything 
good for you. You realise crying isn't a sign a weakness, but it's the sign of a broken 
heart, waiting to rest easy. Time is something everyone has, but most don't realise the
value given to it. 

Your heart accepts the little voice in your mind, your heart tells it to shut up and get on
with the life you have. Your heart grows colder, leaving no mercy for other people, it realises
people who are at the top didn't get it by magic, they earned it with hard work and sacrifice of 
precious time.Your heart becomes wiser, it adapts to changes in life and acknowledges even the 
slightest of movements. 

But all of this leads to a tragic ending. You live your life knowing what happens next. You
spend time with people knowing one they'll leave you because they got bored of you, like some
toy. In the end you regret making your heart like this. So you end it all in one night.